Upstream files are kept verbatim
--------------------------------

The repository root README.md, docs/*, LICENSE, CONTRIBUTING.md, the root
pyproject.toml, assets/* (including demo media and community QR codes), and the
core sources (ga.py, agent_loop.py, agentmain.py, llmcore.py, frontends/*,
memory/*) are upstream GenericAgent files kept at deliberate zero diff so that
upstream updates merge cleanly. They describe and identify the upstream kernel.

The repository's rendered front page is .github/README.md (GitHub README
precedence: .github/ > root), which is the Penglai-branded entry point. Penglai's
only install entry points are install.sh / docker-install.sh / the PyPI
bootstrap (installer/), all pointing at kevinchennewbee/PenglaiAgent.


